item.title: I can connect to the server, and no one else can
item.dc:creator: @Mental_Piracy Mental Piracy
item.description:
@Mental_Piracy wrote:

[quote=“Adelmas, post:12, topic:331915”]Ok.

I have no-ip.

Port is open.

Firewall is off.

Idk how to check if it is on local-host… when i log in on the records it says local-host connected.[/quote]
Localhost is your local pc, ip 127.0.0.1 When you log into your server it may say localhost if your client is set to connect to 127.0.0.1. Maybe the client you gave them connects to 127.0.0.1? That would cause the problem. I just wish you had searched forums a bit more before posting. Also any additional information can help us to help you.

item.dc:creator: @H_tler H¡tler
item.description:
@H_tler wrote:

Well, as dumb as this sounds, it could be true as it happened to my friend. The port you opened (via your router) could be using the wrong IP Address (192.168.0.). [- being your last digit]. He had 192.168.0.3 as the IP and it didn’t work later he found out that 192.168.0.5 was the correct IP and from there it worked.
